-- Germany Coach Says Rooney Ready to Score, Daily Mail Reports: Roundup
-- Alex Duff
-- 2010-06-24T09:51:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/germany-coach-says-rooney-ready-to-score-daily-mail-reports-roundup.html

          
          
             The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links.  
 Rooney’s Form  
 Germany coach  Joachim Loew  said England striker  Wayne Rooney  is “ready to explode” with goals at the World Cup after
failing to score in the three group games, the  Daily Mail 
reported.  
 Rooney was substituted in the second half of England’s 1-0
win against Slovenia yesterday that set up a round-of-16 match
against Germany. “Rooney may not have been a big gun so far but
he is ready to explode,” Loew was quoted as saying.  
 Premier Display  
 Frank Lampard  said England’s players reproduced the
“passion” they show in the Premier League by beating Slovenia
yesterday, the  Daily Mail  reported.  
 “We play that way for our clubs,” the Chelsea midfielder
was quoted as saying. “If we play with those qualities then
we’ve got a chance.”  
 Hodgson Returns  
 Roy Hodgson  is returning to the U.K. today from the World
Cup and hopes to complete a deal to become Liverpool coach, the
 Daily Mirror  reported.  
 The Fulham manager has been working as an analyst in South
Africa for the BBC, the Mirror said.  
 Two Silva Bids  
 Manchester City received permission to hold talks with
Valencia winger  David Silva  with a view to a 30 million-pound
($44.9 million) transfer,  the Sun  reported.  
 Chelsea is also bidding to sign the Spain forward,
according to the  Daily Mail .  
